<%#
  CZID-285 — Layer 3 clearance deny UX. Shown when a user's identity verification did not pass or their
  screening did not come back clear (or is still pending).

  ⚠️ TODO(counsel): the denial copy is a PLACEHOLDER with legal weight — counsel-owned before go-live. A
  screening HIT in particular may carry legal/reporting obligations and its user-facing handling is
  counsel's, not engineering's (design doc §10).

  Non-bypassable by design: NO "continue anyway" link. The only affordances are to retry clearance or to
  sign out. Rendered with HTTP 403.
%>
<div class="export-control-denied" style="max-width: 640px; margin: 96px auto; padding: 0 24px; text-align:center; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; color:#cf222e;">
    <%# TODO(counsel): heading copy %>
    Access denied
  </h1>

  <p style="line-height:1.6; color:#24292f; margin-bottom:28px;">
    <%# TODO(counsel): denial body copy — legal weight %>
    <strong>PLACEHOLDER — pending counsel-approved text.</strong><br />
    Access to export-controlled functions requires a verified, screened identity. Because that clearance
    could not be confirmed, access cannot be granted. [Counsel-owned denial language will replace this text.]
  </p>

  <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; justify-content:center;">
    <%= link_to "Try identity verification again", new_export_control_clearance_path,
                style: "background:#0969da; color:#fff; text-decoration:none; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px;" %>
    <%= link_to "Sign out", auth0_logout_path,
                style: "background:#fff; color:#24292f; border:1px solid #d0d7de; text-decoration:none; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px;" %>
  </div>
</div>
